Combines multiple git repositories as subdirectories into a new repository.
This script performs a full migration, including all branches and tags.

To use this script, change the required variable descriptions at the start of the _git-combine-repos.bash_ script as folows:

    TARGET_REPO     - The name of the new target repository to create
    WORKSPACE       - The directory where the 'old' projects will be
                      cloned into and the new repository will be created.
    PROJECTS        - For every project to migrate a ' [CODE]=project ' line.
    REPOSITORIES    - For every project a ' [CODE]=repository ' line.
    MERGE_PROJECTS  - The project codes of all repositories to migrate.
